  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PCM: Capital Impact Exchange (CAPx)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(USAID Economic Growth, Education and Environment (E3)):  The Capital Impact Exchange (CAPx) program is a new blended finance learning activity aimed at identifying evidence and prioritizing learning to inform USAID&apos;s approaches to mobilizing private capital. This mechanism is the first award under the INVEST+ Basic Ordering Agreements platform which enables Missions, Bureaus, and Operating Units direct engagement with innovative approaches to mobilizing private capital for development outcomes. CAPx is designed to examine the way USAID promotes capital mobilization, creates incentives for lending and investment, and leverages private sector involvement. The activity will generate new perspectives, methods, and evidence-based approaches to create better blended finance solutions that can be incorporated to make USAID&apos;s programming across any sector, any geography more robust. FY 2019 funds will advance the knowledge base, generate and analyze evidence, and adaptively inform USAID&apos;s efforts to catalyze private investment for development outcomes.  .Activities expected to be undertaken will include an evaluation of the Agency&apos;s existing portfolio of blended finance activities, evidence and learning practices from external industry leaders and the design of a learning agenda which will continually guide USAID&apos;s efforts to mobilize private capital. Finally, the learning agenda will be used to guide direct technical assistance in monitoring, evaluation and learning to Missions, Bureaus and Operating Units undertaking design and implementation of blended finance activities. .</narrative>
  </description>
